@node Read "Information on miscellaneous stuff"

RnDefIco was written on an Amiga 4000/030 with 4MB RAM using SAS/C 6.50.
RnDefIco has been tested on the above machine and I haven't bumped into
any Enforcer hits anymore. (My MMU actually works!)
RnDefIco should function on any Amiga running Kickstart 2.0 or higher.
This has not been tested. Please report any and all problems to me.
I had several chances of optimizing the code for 68020 and above, but opted
to still make it 68000 compatible. Depending on response this might change
with newer versions.

I (Aleksi Suhonen) am now (13.6.1994 19:38:49.015) 18 years old and going
